# Tailwind CSS Component Rule

Apply these patterns in React component files:

- Keep Tailwind classes close to the element they style unless extracted into a shared component.
- For repeated UI patterns, create reusable components instead of copying long class strings.
- For conditional classes, use a clear class-composition helper pattern instead of string concatenation.
- Keep variants predictable: base classes first, then conditional and responsive variants.
- Include keyboard and focus-visible states on interactive components.
- Prefer existing design tokens and shared primitives before introducing one-off utilities.
